+{"id":"bd-7i0gb","title":"PORT: strtonum (OpenBSD bounded decimal parser)","description":"OpenBSD strtonum(nptr, minval, maxval, errstr) parses nptr as a decimal long long integer constrained to [minval, maxval] and returns the value plus an opaque error category through *errstr (NULL on success, "invalid"/"too small"/"too large"/"out of range" on failure). Used by OpenBSD utilities (sshd, pf, bgpd) for safer numeric parsing than strtoll(3) — no errno fiddling, no overflow gotchas, range check baked in. Currently missing from frankenlibc-abi/stdlib_abi.rs. Ship: pure-safe core::stdlib::strtonum::parse returning Result<i64, StrtonumError> with Invalid/TooSmall/TooLarge/InvalidRange variants + thin abi shim that maps the error to OpenBSD-canonical static error strings.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:37:06.767215232Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:44:45.790635576Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:44:45.788730601Z","close_reason":"shipped: core::stdlib::strtonum + stdlib_abi::strtonum; 25+12 tests; clippy-clean; rch-built","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
