+{"id":"bd-jbemm","title":"PORT: getpeereid (BSD Unix-socket peer credentials)","description":"BSD getpeereid(s, euid, egid) returns the effective uid + gid of the peer of a connected Unix-domain socket. On Linux this is a thin wrapper over getsockopt(s, SOL_SOCKET, SO_PEERCRED, &ucred, &len) — read the kernel-supplied credentials struct and split out the uid/gid fields. Returns 0 on success (writes *euid and *egid), -1 with errno on failure. Used by sshd, postfix, sudo, and other privilege-separating daemons that need to identify the local user on the other end of a socket without a userland authentication round trip. Currently missing entirely from frankenlibc-abi.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T04:06:23.236695254Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T04:06:23.236695254Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
