+{"id":"bd-jp7nt","title":"PORT: reallocf + arc4random_addrandom + arc4random_stir (BSD/libbsd compat)","description":"BSD reallocf(ptr, size) = realloc(ptr, size) but free(ptr) on failure. Defeats the classic "realloc loses your buffer on ENOMEM" leak that requires every caller to either save the original pointer or check for NULL before reassigning. Plus arc4random_addrandom(dat, datlen) and arc4random_stir() — deprecated OpenBSD entropy-mixing primitives that modern arc4random keeps as stubs because the underlying CSPRNG is reseeded automatically; programs linked against libbsd often reference them so we expose no-ops to satisfy the linker. All three live in stdlib_abi.rs / unistd_abi.rs as thin shims over the existing realloc / free / no-op infrastructure; no new core module needed.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:58:49.468737452Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T04:02:49.601837858Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T04:02:49.599904258Z","close_reason":"shipped: reallocf + arc4random_addrandom/stir; 6 tests; clippy-clean; rch-built","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-jqy64","title":"[MODE-1][HIGH] symbolic correctness: c11threads create/join backend mismatch","description":"[MODE-1][HIGH] symbolic correctness: C11 thread create and join backend contract is internally inconsistent

Validated by current remote gate failure:
- `env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_target_frankenlibc_cod rch exec -- cargo test --workspace --all-targets`
- failing suite: `crates/frankenlibc-abi/tests/c11threads_abi_test.rs`

Concrete mismatch:
- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/c11threads_abi.rs:72-110` calls `crate::pthread_abi::pthread_create`, which prefers host `pthread_create` whenever `resolved_thread_create_raw()` is available (`crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/pthread_abi.rs:1991-2015`).
- `crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/c11threads_abi.rs:118-124` then calls `crate::pthread_abi::pthread_join`.
- `pthread_join` is hard-routed to `native_pthread_join` (`crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/pthread_abi.rs:2019-2021`), which only accepts handles present in `THREAD_HANDLE_REGISTRY` and returns `ESRCH` otherwise (`crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/pthread_abi.rs:1409-1445`).

For host-created threads, the symbolic contract `join(create(f, arg)) = THRD_SUCCESS plus propagated return value` is broken: the handle identity model used by `create` is not the one consumed by `join`.

Observed fallout already matches that model break:
- `test_thrd_create_join`
- `test_thrd_join_propagates_zero`
- `test_thrd_join_propagates_negative`
- `test_thrd_join_propagates_large`

Fix direction:
- make C11 thread lifecycle choose one backend consistently across create, join, detach, self, and equal, or
- teach `pthread_join` to resolve host-thread handles through the host path instead of assuming every successful create registered a native handle.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-04-22T08:45:20.777550950Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T03:30:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T03:30:00Z","close_reason":"Already fixed: commit 138c07c3 made pthread_join delegate to host for non-managed handles. 37/37 c11threads_abi_test pass. Verified round 2.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["c11threads","modes","review","symbolic"]}
