+{"id":"bd-zt2w1","title":"PORT: getprogname + setprogname (BSD program-name accessors)","description":"BSD getprogname()/setprogname(name) — read or set the program short name used by warn/err/syslog/fprintf-progname diagnostics. NetBSD/OpenBSD/glibc 2.41+ all expose these as the canonical way for tools (and libraries) to query/override the basename of argv[0] without having to know about the glibc-specific program_invocation_short_name global. Currently missing entirely from frankenlibc-abi. Implementation: thin wrappers over startup_abi::program_invocation_short_name AtomicPtr — getprogname loads the pointer (returning a fallback "" pointer if the slot is NULL), setprogname computes the basename (last "/" component) of the caller-supplied C string and stores that pointer back. The caller owns the storage per BSD setprogname contract.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T03:50:50.479608424Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:54:59.038195864Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:54:59.036311407Z","close_reason":"shipped: startup_abi::getprogname + setprogname; 7 tests; clippy-clean; rch-built","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
